reviewText: I saw this a few years ago when it was released on TV, and of course like all the Monster High movies this is a must have in your MH collection.

We love Monster High! I don't know why it took so long to release this movie on DVD, but better late than never. If you're a fan of Monster High be sure to check this movie out. You won't be disappointed. My only complaint is that instead of Monster High shorts as bonus features, you get Ever After High. YUCK!
Other than that it's a fang-tastic movie!
Now we're just waiting for the release of 'Boo York, Boo York' in September.

My daughter and I have watched all of the monster high movies together. We have loved them all. Every monster high movie teaches a lesson in some sort of way. In this monster high movie the lesson is always stay true to yourself and don't become some thing your not. This movie has its funny parts and cute romance scenes. It was a really fun and enjoying movie to watch. If you are a monster high fan I would definitely suggest you watch this movie.

I am a big Monster High fan, and I've seen all the movies and most of the first two seasons of the internet show. I bought it on Amazon for the whooping $5, but I took the risk in anticipation of the quality of clever writing and humor I expect. But it certainly wasn't worth that. Saw it once, maybe I'll see it again later but it felt like it was either fallen apart, a mish-mash of stories, or was a rushed project with greater potential.

I recommend the other movies though!
